		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> <date>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> May&#47;62</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I was thinking of writing<lb/> you in answer to your two letters when I got<lb/> this week your esteemed lines of <date>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi></date>. ult.  You<lb/> must excuse the delay&#44; but I understood that<lb/> <persName>Mr. M. D. Osorio</persName> wrote you lately&#44; and too little<lb/> transpires here to tax you with a frequent cor&#8222;<lb/> respondence.  I presume that he has given you<lb/> all information from our <placeName>Island</placeName>&#59; however I<lb/> send you a slip from the &#8220;Times&#44;&#8221; bring copy of<lb/> an address presented by the members of our con&#8222;<lb/>gregation to <persName>Rev. Rabbi Chumaceiro</persName> on his last<lb/> visit here.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Herewith please find <persName>Osorio&#44; Wright &#38; Co.&#39;s</persName> Dft.<lb/> &#64; 60 D&#47;S on <persName>Dovale &#38; Co.</persName> <placeName>N. Y</placeName> for &#36;66.06&#44; for acct. due<lb/> you by me as p. annexed statement&#44; and &#36;20. in&#8222;<lb/>cluded by <persName>Mr. Correa</persName>.  I could get no more than</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>&#36;8. for the Pentateuch 12 mo&#59; and there are now 3 sets<lb/> 8 vo. left.  The three Bibles having been sold&#44; I shall&#44;<lb/> if convenient to you&#44; be willing to receive as many<lb/> more.  Perhaps also two or three copies of the Daily<lb/> Prayers in the cheaper bindings would also be<lb/> <sic>saleable</sic>.  Have the goodness to send me a copy<lb/> of the first series of your sermons&#44; and also name<lb/> me some others of your publications&#44; for it there<lb/> are among them any which I have not read&#44;<lb/> would like to get one or two.  Young <persName>Mr. O.</persName> told me<lb/> some weeks ago that he had got several subscri&#8222;<lb/>bers for the work which you are translating&#44; which<lb/> is more than I would have expected.  If you can<lb/> find time please answer his letter.  I regret to<lb/> notice your observations about the Occident.  I<lb/> have not yet seen <persName>Mr. Myers</persName> since&#44; but from the<lb/> answer which he gave me some months ago&#44; doubt<lb/> that he will be able to get any subscribers.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My sister left for <placeName>Panama</placeName> shortly after her<lb/> marriage&#44; but I have written your remembrance<lb/> to her.  My Father unties with me in best regards.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Respy. Yours&#44; <persName role="author">David M. Pizal</persName></p>
